The paper discusses deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and speech recognition (cs.SD). The focus of the paper is on quantization, which is a technique used to reduce the memory requirements of deep neural networks, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses current challenges and trends in quantized neural networks, which could be relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.AR) as well.
